Aaroan, Drooood of the 60th Ring, Tribunal,Guild: The Companions<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usabbyfkb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sabbyFKB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 12:25:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1>  By &quot;POA&quot; you mean??<br>
<br>
<br>
 I dont wanna assume you mean Plan of Air, b/c i cant figure why anyone would go there anymore except for a quick epic raid. You can get that done in one trip tho.  YOu must mean something else.<br>
<br>
<br>
  Anyhow any large, raid focused guild would be in Sleepers, ToV, and killing brood dragons at least once a week. In addition they would have full or nearly full ToV(Kael or Skyshrine), and be done with Veeshans Peak for the most part.<br>
<br>
<br>
 Anyhow I have 9 slots free of +wis items and I still have problems with my wisdom being to high.  I really cant see anyone with access to the high-end gear wanting more than 95-100 base wis. The stats just dont add up.  Why would you want to run around with even 1 point over 200 wis??<br>
<br>
  Sab <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquigsby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quigsby</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 1:52:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1> Coming from a druid that has 115 base wis, and has seen the world.. a lot; I would say that having 115 base wis is very benificial for me.  Therefore, I don't need to throw some lower ac/resist item in a place where wis would go.  Therefore, I have 200 wis now, and 858 self buffed AC.  This is with minimal plane gear, seeing as my guild is going after levels and epics at the moment.  Also, having 15 or so planable druids doesn't help.  Anyways, I find it benificial :P <p><font color="#006600"><font size=+2>Quigsby Quickfoot</font></font>
<br><font color="#FF0000"><font size=+1>59th Preserver of Zebuxoruk</font></font>
<br><a href="http://www.requiemofsouls.com"><font color="663399"><font size=+1>Requiem of Souls</font></font></a><br>
"Thought this be madness, yet there is method in't."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uloeganwolfheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loegan Wolfheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 2:04:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1> Put all your points into wis, which leaves 5 extra. If you have less than 100 agi, I would put them there. You will notice a big difference when you go from 99 to 100 agi. Anything over 100 won't effect much unless you get to an insane amount for a druid like 150.<br>
<br>
Dex is good for procs and the same break points apply (100, 150, 200), but unless you have the fantasy of being a melee druid at high levels, you won't be wanting to choose dex gear over ac/wis gear, especially since it takes huge gains in dex to make you proc more.<br>
<br>
Sta... it's good to break 100, but even then I don't think it makes a huge difference.<br>
<br>
In the end game, I have found that resists and ac make the most difference, so the higher your wisdom, the more you can afford to give up for resist gear. Grant it, level makes a huge impact on resists, but you still need the highest resists you can get. In battles with dragons, believe me resists are your best friend. <p><br>
<center> <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=5417">Loegan Wolfheart </A><A HREF="http://www.the-elitists.com/">(The Elitists)</A> <br>
<center>Druid of the 60th Ring <br>
<center> Resident of The Tribunal <br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugwynetwoodsister.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gwynet Woodsister</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 6:35:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1> Just one comment : every player in the end game isn't in a uber guild.<br>
<br>
Thank you <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhyrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/01 6:52:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1> High level doesnt mean end game. I just means high level. End game means fighting in the hardest zones facing the hardest chalenges put in the game by varent.<br>
<br>
When you have access to the best equip in the game you are going to find your wis high always, your HP high almost always, your resists high almost always, and your hp/mana high almost always. You will still have extra stuff to switch in the buff what you need at the time. <br>
<br>
Oh and AC wont save you very much verse uber mobs but when you are fighting in reletivly high level zones with small numbers you can find charming some pretty powerful mobs helps a lot. Being able to root off and recharm mobs hitting for around 210 ie in SG/WW etc you will notice the AC starts to help. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hyrineq/hysig01.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unosforatunytewind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nosforatu Nytewind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/01 7:58:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=27>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.sandislehawaii.com/images/nos.jpg width=150 height=250></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1> Putting all points into wis is always the benefit.  Why? <br>
<br>
Even without a thurg BP and such, I hold 201 wisdom.. barely.<br>
<br>
But, my AC is 901 and my HP is 2017 self buffed at level 58.<br>
<br>
Plus, I have the benefit of using a fungi tunic which I feel has saved my butt more than once.  In all honesty, it would take a lot of convincing to remove the fungi tunic.  I can quad kite a lot safer now because I heal myself about 2 health bubbs while kiting.<br>
<br>
All in all, with my setup, I dont see why anyone would choose less than the full wisdom.  You all say, I put 10 points in wisdom and blah blah... my AC and HP rocks because I can afford to wear TWO +6AC +65 HP rings... which is a larger benefit than a few points in agil and stamina can match.  Hell 20 points of stamina from the Othmir Totem is only about 70 hp... thats barely more than one of my rings..<br>
<br>
This makes sense right? <br>
<br>
<br>
-Nosforatu<br>
 58 Druid<br>
 Legendary <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usabbyfkb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sabbyFKB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/01 12:21:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1>  No it doesnt make sense. Unless Thurgardin armor(ick) is the endgame for you.  If you plan on scaling  up to the quest armor from ToV your gonna have way to much wisdom.<br>
<br>
<br>
  Sab <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usabbyfkb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sabbyFKB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/01 12:27:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1>  ohhh almost forgot.<br>
<br>
<br>
  Wear the rings AND the othmir prexus totem. If you sit around deciding not to add a piece of gear b/c some other piece of gear your wearing gives the same or less hp/mana, your setup is gonna be messed. Would you refuse to use a belt that gave 80 mana because your leggings gave 90?  <br>
<br>
 A 60 druid with 100 base wis should be able to manage at least 9 equipped slots totally free of +wis items.  I do, and thats why I have more hps and AC than you Nos. However, lately I have been dumping some hps/ac for mana. I still keep hps at the 2100 mark and AC over 900, but mana seems to make more of a difference after that benchmark.  Raid buffing to 4k hps and 1k AC is plenty good enough.  Lately i outlive my mana, surely not a good sign!<br>
<br>
<br>
 Sab <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujambone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jambone</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 11:24:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1> I wonder how many of us were we to start over and create a character designed specifically for &quot;end game&quot;, would again select a druid?  Don't get me wrong, I do find ways to fit in and make myself useful but I bet that the extra warrior/cleric/shaman... you pick the class, would make more impact than the perfectly balanced druid could ever hope to accomplish in an epic encounter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 12:21:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3258.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Starting stats playing for end game </span><hr size=1> I started as a halfling and put most of my points in strength with wisom at 100.<br>
<br>
